We recommended the Local Chief Executive to:
Direct the Designated General Service Officer to review and monitor the Monthly Report of Official Travel and prepare and submit Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption for various types of motor vehicles showing the total distance travelled, total fuel used and the normal fuel consumption of each vehicle;
Require all Municipal Drivers to accomplish the trip tickets with complete information and to prepare and submit the Report on Official Travels on a monthly basis;
Rectify the appropriation of fuel expenses to Mayor’s Office and distribute part of the budget to specific office assigned with motor vehicles for the ensuing year.

We recommended the Local Chief Executive to –
Direct the Bids and Awards Committee to comply with the standard format of bidding documents and ensure that all provisions contained therein are provided in accordance with the prescribed form and content;
Direct the BAC to set precise, complete and clear technical specifications, and a clear statement of the required standards.

We recommended the Local Chief Executive to:
Direct the Bids and Awards Committee to comply with the standard format of bidding documents.
Direct the BAC through its Secretariat to –
Truthfully post every Invitation to Bid, Notices of Award, Notices to Proceed and approved contract within the required media and within the specified required time for wider bid opportunities of private contracting parties and for timely information of public of the results of the procurement;
Publish in the Phil-GEPS website and agency website the Notices of Award, Notices to Proceed and approved contracts for the procurement done through public bidding and all instances of alternative modes of procurement, except for contracts with ABC of ₱50,000.00 and below; and
Issue certification on the posting of the same in any conspicuous place in the premises of the Procuring Entity.
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that the print out copies of postings in Phil-GEPS website are included among the supporting documents for payment of the first progress billing and ensure that all the payments of contract billings for infrastructure projects are supported with the Certificate of Materials Quality Test/Materials Test Results to assure quality of materials introduced in the project;
Direct the BAC to ensure that files are kept of bid notices posted in the PhilGEPS website with the “Active Status”;
Instruct the BAC to require the contractors to submit the DOLE duly approved CSHP before the approval and signing of the contract;
Require the BAC Secretariat to submit all lacking supporting documents of contracts as well as to ensure that contracts together with all their integral parts forming part thereof will be submitted within five (5) days after execution of the contract.
(a) submit to Audit Team the complete set of approved plans and specifications on projects, or satisfactory explanation in the absence thereof. Henceforth, ensure that the required detailed engineering, including the preparation of plans and drawings are sufficiently carried out before any bidding and award of contract; (b) require the contractor to submit the DOLE- approved CSHP on projects; (c) provide a written explanation on the noted absence or delayed posting of tarpaulin signboards on subject projects, and remind the contractors and project engineers of the timely posting of tarpaulin signboards in future projects in strict compliance with COA Circular 2013-004; and (d) together with BAC Chairperson and Municipal Accountant, provide satisfactory justifications that would prove the validity and propriety of subject transactions noted with inconsistent and insufficient information in the supporting documents.
Head of the BAC Secretariat to provide certification on posting of bid opportunities and award by indicating the actual duration and place/site of posting in the future procurements.

We recommended the Local Chief Executive to:
Direct the MDRRMO to fast track the implementation of projects by close coordination with the GSO, devise a monitoring tool of all projects, and to review the PPA’s especially those from previous years to determine their responsiveness to the needs of the Municipality or to meet the purpose of the fund;
Ensure efficient and effective implementation of all programmed projects identified during the budget year to optimize the utilization of the fund and to warrant that goals and objectives of reducing disaster risk and enhancing disaster preparedness and response capabilities be achieved.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
Require the MPDC to conduct a thorough planning for the implementation of development projects by clearly identifying the project procurement timelines as laid down in the Project Procurement Management Plan and Annual Procurement Plan or their equivalent;
